Description: Fragment of lip, neck and oval, tapering handle to sharp turn of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with torch symbol.
Curator's comments: Ink, deleted, '101̣'. Name Olympos. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0394.33.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (205)
